I find the translate function, though very simple, rather elegant JS:<p><pre><code>  AI.prototype.translate = function(move) {
   return {
      0: &#x27;up&#x27;,
      1: &#x27;right&#x27;,
      2: &#x27;down&#x27;,
      3: &#x27;left&#x27;
    }[move];
  }
</code></pre>
Ref: <a href="https://github.com/ov3y/2048-AI/blob/master/js/ai.js#L230" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/ov3y/2048-AI/blob/master/js/ai.js#L230</a>

I am working on a MVP and am going for an elegant look. I have the <p> in Georgia 22px but would like something a little less common. Georgia is a nice font but it is everywhere.<p>My current main fonts are:<p><pre><code>      p { font-family: Georgia, Palatino, &quot;Palatino Linotype&quot;, Times, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; 
          font-size: 22px; }

      h2 { font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; 
          font-size: 22px; }
</code></pre>
Has anyone found a font combination with an elegant, &quot;classical&quot; look?<p>Edited: for spacing
